    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Jan 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>— 1876</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am much obliged for your kind gift of six copies of the “Garden”, with a drawing of myself &amp; a notice of my works.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> This notice is drawn up in the most generous spirit &amp; is highly honourable to me.</p>
<p>I thank the writer very sincerely &amp; remain | Dear Sir | Yours very faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Robinson had founded the <hi rend="italic">Garden</hi>, a weekly illustrated horticultural magazine, in 1871. CD’s engraved portrait appeared as the frontispiece to the supplement to the issue of 1 January 1876, together with an unsigned account of his botanical publications (<hi rend="italic">Garden</hi> 8 (1875): xi–xii).</note>
        </div>        
            
